The State of the Nation Address 2020 • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. CAPE TOWN - President Cyril Ramaphosa is set to deliver the State of the Nation Address (Sona) on Thursday. Ramaphosa will have to inspire confidence in South Africans. He is expected to address the high unemployment rate, the country's contracting economy and troubled State-Owned Entreprises among other issues. The Sona will include guests such as former presidents Thabo Mbeki, FW de Klerk, Kgalema Motlanthe and former National Assembly Speaker Frene Ginwala.